  text:"Suppose Mary's cross-price elasticity of demand between good X and good Y is 2. If the price of good Y increases by 10%, which of the following statements is true?",
  opts:["Quantity demanded for good X increases by 20%","Quantity demanded for good X decreases by 10%","Quantity demanded for good X decreases by 20%","Quantity demanded for good X increases by 10%"],
  answer:0,
  explain:"Cross-price elasticity = %ΔQd_X / %ΔP_Y. So %ΔQd_X = 2 × 10% = 20% increase. Positive cross-price elasticity means X and Y are substitutes — when Y gets pricier, people switch to X!",
  catMsg:"Pie Cookie says: Think of it like treats — if one brand gets expensive, you switch to the other! 🐱"
},
{
  id:2, topic:"Elasticity",
  text:"Which of the following graphs illustrates the changes in the price elasticity of supply over time? (SR = short run, LR = long run)",
