  explain:"MU = change in TU. Working through: TU(1)=5, TU(2)=5+2=7, TU(3)=7+1=8. So MU(4) = TU(4)−TU(3) = 8−8 = 0. The 4th hotdog is the satiation point — total utility is maximized and eating one more adds nothing!",
  catMsg:"Pie Cookie says: Even I stop eating after the perfect amount of treats... okay, that's not true. But John should! 🐱"
