  explain:"Quota rent = (P_quota − P_world) × quantity of imports under quota = ($80 − $50) × (150−120) = $30 × 80... The quota allows a specific quantity of imports, and importers earn the price difference on each unit. Quota rent = $2,400.",
  catMsg:"Pie Cookie says: Quota rent is the profit that goes to whoever holds the import licenses — free money! 🐱"
},
{
  id:20, topic:"Elasticity",
  text:"The price of a laptop increases by 10% and quantity demanded decreases by 4%. What is the price elasticity of demand?",
